Example
Return the port number of the current URL:

Copy
let x = "Port: " + location.port;

Description
The port property gets and sets the port number the server uses for a URL.

If the port number is not specified in the URL or if it is the scheme's default port - like 80, some browsers will display 0 or nothing.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
port	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Return the port property:

Copy
let a = location.port;
Set the port property:

Copy
location.port = port;
Property Values
Value	Type	Description
port	String	Specifies the port number of the URL
Return Value
A String, representing the port number of a URL.

If the port number is not specified or if it is the scheme's default port (like 80 or 443), an empty string is returned.
